============================================================
PHASE 17 OBJECTIVE
============================================================

Build the autonomous enterprise optimization layer for zDash.

Main goals:

1. Add predictive SRE engine
2. Add incident prediction and anomaly forecasting
3. Add SLO error-budget burn forecasting
4. Add capacity planning engine
5. Add workload placement recommendation engine
6. Add cloud/infra cost optimization shell
7. Add FinOps dashboard and savings recommendations
8. Add customer health prediction
9. Add churn/expansion signal model
10. Add partner growth intelligence
11. Add marketplace ranking and promotion recommendations
12. Add reseller performance analytics
13. Add regional expansion recommendation engine
14. Add enterprise renewal and account risk scoring
15. Add executive command center API
16. Add quarterly business review report generator
17. Add optimization action approval workflow
18. Add autonomous recommendation queue
19. Add safe execution planner for approved optimizations
20. Add tests, docs, runbooks, and final acceptance gates

IMPORTANT SAFETY RULES:
- Do not enable live trading by default.
- Do not enable real IoT actions by default.
- Do not enable real social posting by default.
- Do not bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Do not bypass content approval checks.
- Do not bypass tenant isolation.
- Do not bypass billing entitlements.
- Do not bypass governance policies.
- Do not bypass final GA safety gates.
- Do not bypass data residency enforcement.
- Predictive systems must be advisory by default.
- Autonomous optimization must not execute destructive changes without approval.
- Cost optimization must not delete resources by default.
- Capacity planning must not scale production systems automatically unless explicitly approved.
- Partner growth automation must not send real outreach or modify billing by default.
- Marketplace ranking must be transparent and auditable.
- No secrets, credentials, tokens, broker credentials, raw prompts, raw customer data, or private payloads may be logged, exported, synced, or displayed.
- All prediction outputs must include confidence and explanation.
- Forecasts are estimates, not guarantees.

