============================================================
IMPORTANT IMPLEMENTATION RULES
============================================================

- Do not use pseudocode.
- Do not skip files.
- Do not remove Phase 1–16 behavior.
- Keep all existing backend tests passing.
- Keep all existing frontend tests passing.
- Keep mobile tests passing.
- Keep desktop tests passing.
- Keep SDK tests passing.
- Use typed Python where reasonable.
- Use TypeScript types.
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.x style.
- Never hardcode secrets.
- Never expose secrets in frontend, mobile, desktop, SDKs, logs, reports, docs, exports, or prediction outputs.
- Never log API keys, KMS key refs, runner tokens, broker credentials, cloud credentials, or private payloads.
- Never store raw customer payloads in predictive outputs.
- Never enable live trading by default.
- Never enable real social posting by default.
- Never enable real IoT power actions by default.
- Never bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Never bypass content approval checks.
- Never bypass tenant isolation.
- Never bypass billing entitlements.
- Never bypass governance policies.
- Never bypass final GA safety gates.
- Never bypass data residency enforcement.
- Never automatically execute optimization changes by default.
- Never delete or scale resources automatically by default.
- Never change customer billing automatically.
- Never boost uncertified marketplace listings.
- Keep predictive systems advisory by default.
- Keep all forecasts explainable, confidence-scored, and marked as estimates.
- Keep code modular and ready for Phase 18: autonomous AI boardroom, ecosystem simulation, and strategic planning intelligence.

